---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import SEO from '../components/SEO.astro';
import ForwardLink from '../components/ForwardLink.astro';

const pageTitle = 'About NextGen Wargame';
const pageDescription =
  'Why NextGen Wargame exists and how TJ Taijeron turns governed AI workflows into usable training products.';
---

<PageLayout>
  <SEO
    slot="head"
    title={pageTitle}
    description={pageDescription}
    type="profile"
  />

  <section class="about-hero" aria-labelledby="about-title">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1 id="about-title">NextGen Wargame documents how TJ Taijeron turns messy training problems into usable products.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      The site exists to make the work legible: problem framing, source governance, AI-assisted production, controller-facing tools, execution validation, and iteration from evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bio-section">
    <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
    <p>
      AI output is easy to generate and hard to trust. This site shows the operating layer around the output: how a design problem is framed, how source truth is controlled, how tools and workflows are built, and how the result is validated before the claim is made.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bio-section">
    <h2>The identity</h2>
    <p>
      TJ works as a design/product/operator hybrid: define the problem, build the workflow, govern the model, protect the review gate, and make the artifact usable by the people who have to run it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bio-section">
    <h2>Why games matter</h2>
    <p>
      The game-design question is always the same: what decision is the player making, with what information, and with what consequence. That framing translates directly into staff training, controller design, and adjudication structure.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bio-section">
    <h2>What the repo contains</h2>
    <p>
      Projects show the proof layer. Decisions show the governance layer. Methods show the repeatable process. Together they explain not just what was built, but how it was made credible and reusable.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bio-section games-section">
    <h2>The background behind it</h2>
    <p>
      TJ's background in military training, simulations, and exercise delivery is why the site is organized around execution reality rather than abstract AI claims. The emphasis stays on usable products, controlled workflows, and learning under pressure.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-cta">
    <div>
      <h2>Start with the proof</h2>
      <p>
        CADE is the capstone project. The methods page explains the repeatable process behind it.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-links">
      <ForwardLink href="/methods" text="View methods and capabilities" />
      <ForwardLink href="/projects/cade" text="Read the CADE case study" variant="muted" />
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    padding: 2rem 0 3rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .lead {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.25rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .bio-section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
  }

  .bio-section h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .bio-section p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .bio-section p + p {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .games-section {
    background: var(--color-bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  .games-section h2 {
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .about-cta {
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .about-cta h2 {
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .about-cta p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .cta-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    min-width: max-content;
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .about-cta {
      align-items: flex-start;
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .cta-links {
      min-width: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
